OL,3,CQuick-thinking lifeguards save 13-year-
OL,4,Cold stuck in riptide
OL,6,FA team of quick-thinking lifeguards
OL,7,Fwho rescued a 13-year-old boy from a
OL,8,Friptide off the Cornish coast just as
OL,9,Fthey were packing up say the situation
OL,10,Fcould have been "much worse".
OL,12,FRNLI member George Hudson was first to
OL,13,Frespond to the emergency in
OL,14,FPerranporth on Thursday 23 May,
OL,15,Fpaddling out on a rescue board,
OL,16,Fdragging the boy to safety and
OL,17,Fperforming CPR on him.
OL,19,FThe incident happened at 6.05pm - just
OL,20,Fas lifeguards were finishing for the
OL,21,Fday and packing away their flags.
